<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--CrutchKilling     07-28 0182</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Crutch Killing,0186</SECOND>
<HEAD>Woman, 80, Accused of Battering Husband With Crutch</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TRIKALA, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An 80-year-old woman who allegedly beat
her husband with a crutch during an argument over their will has
been charged with his death, police say.
   Stavroula Plexidas was arrested Wednesday in Megalochori, a
small farming village on this outskirts of this town in central
Greece, and charged with the murder of her husband, Nikolaos, 78.
   Plexidas was arrested after her dying husband told police that
she had beaten him with her wooden crutch as he lay in bed Tuesday
night after an argument over their estate, a police spokesman said
Thursday, speaking on condition of anonymity.
   Nikolaos Plexidas died in hospital on Wednesday of a heart
attack and an autopsy also showed lacerations on his neck and legs,
the spokesman said, requesting anonymity in accordance with Greek
practice.
   Mrs. Plexidas told arresting officers that her husband fell off
his bed and struck his head on the floor, the spokesman said.
   He said the suspect had circulatory problems and could not walk
without the support of crutches.
</TEXT>
