<HEAD>Man Sentenced For Desecrating U.S. Flag</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Flag Burning</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CATAWISSA, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who while drunk yanked from the
ground miniature American flags planted along a street has been
sentenced to six months in prison and fined $200 for flag
desecration.
   William Frank Erlston, 22, was sentenced Thursday by District
Justice William L. Breech.
   Police said Erlston discarded the miniature American flags,
planted by members of the Veterans of Foreign Wars for the Fourth
of July. Erlston had been drunk and apparently was not making a
political statement, police said.
   The U.S. Supreme Court recently upheld the right of political
protesters to burn flags as a protected form of free speech. But
Erlston did not use that defense, and instead pleaded guilty to
flag desecration, which in Pennsylvania carries a maximum penalty
of two years in prison and a fine of $5,000.
