<FILEID>AP-NR-07-28-89 1115EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r a PM-FreewaySniper     07-28 0181</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Freeway Sniper,0185</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police Say Sniper Victim Trails Suspect, Sees Killing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who was a target of a freeway
sniper sped after the suspect and then watched in horror as the
gunman pulled alongside another auto and shot the driver to death,
police said.
   Charlie A. Stevens, 20, of Oakland, was booked on one charge
each of murder and attempted murder after the witness identified
him as the gunman in the shootings early Thursday, said Lt. Mike
Sims.
   Raymond August, 28, of Oakland, died of multiple bullet wounds
in the attack, which occurred about two miles from where
36-year-old Lori Anne Rochon was fatally wounded July 6 as she
drove on the freeway.
   The witness, a 24-year-old Oakland man who asked police not to
release his name, said the gunman shot at him from a passing car
and missed.
   The witness turned off his headlights and followed the suspect
to a freeway exit and then called police.
   Officers spotted a car parked near the freeway that fit the
description provided by the witness, Sims said.
</TEXT>
