<HEAD>50 Feared Drowned As Ferry Collides With Cattle Boat</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A ferry carrying 200 passengers
collided with a cattle boat on a southern Bangladesh river and
sank, police said Friday, and at least 50 people were feared
drowned.
   The collision occurred Thursday between the ferry M.L. Prince
Boira and the M.V. Leo on the Pangushi River near Bagerhat, about
85 miles south of Dhaka, police said.
   The M.V. Leo was slightly damaged but did not sink, police said.
   Ten bodies had been recovered by Friday.
   A police officer supervising rescue operations said 125
passengers swam ashore and 25 others were rescued by fishermen. The
captains of the boats survived, and they were being questioned by
investigators, he said.
