<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Nazi     07-28 0123</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Nazi,0125</SECOND>
<HEAD>Fugitive Nazi War Criminal Returned to West Germany</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERN, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fugitive Nazi war criminal Gottfried
Weise was extradited to West Germany on Friday to serve a life term
in prison for the murder of at least three inmates of the Auschwitz
concentration camp.
   Weise, 69, had fled his country in April shortly before the
German supreme court confirmed a lower court verdict against him.
He was arrested on an international warrant Tuesday in the Swiss
town of Thun, where he had been hospitalized under a false name
after suffering a stroke.
   On Thursday, he agreed to be extradited without formal
proceedings. The Swiss Justice Ministry said Weise left Bern in the
company of German officials and a physician.
