<HEAD>Police Find Explosives in City</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELFAST, Northern Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police Friday discovered 160
pounds of homemade explosives and various other bomb-making
equipment they believed were intended for IRA use, a spokesman said.
   The cache was discovered as part of a search of houses in the
mainly Roman Catholic Ardoyne area of the city, said the spokesman,
speaking anonymously.
   One man, who was not identified, was detained and was ``helping
with police inquiries,'' the police spokesman said.
   Police believed the items, which included detonation cords and
chemicals, were for use by the outlawed Irish Republican Army.
   The mainly Roman Catholic IRA is fighting to oust the British
from the province and unite it with the Republic of Ireland.
