<HEAD>Next Mission to Space Station Set for September</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The next manned mission to the Soviet space
station Mir will start in mid-September and take two cosmonauts up
for several months of research and a space walk, Tass said Friday.
   The space station has been vacant since April, in part to save
money.
   Tass said two crews are training for the flight: Col. Alexander
Viktorenko and Alexander Serebov; and Col. Anatoly Solovyov and A.
Balandin, a space rookie.
