<HEAD>Audrey Hepburn Will Add `Always' To Her Credits</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Academy Award-winning actress Audrey Hepburn
plans to add ``Always'' to her movie credits.
   Miss Hepburn has signed on to take part in the Steven Spielberg
film _ the story of a romance that grows while many of the
characters are fighting forest fires.
   She will join a cast that already includes Richard Dreyfuss,
Holly Hunter, John Goodman and Brad Johnson.
   ``Always'' is an Amblin Entertainment production for Universal
Pictures-United Artists and is to be released in December.
   Miss Hepburn won a best actress Oscar in 1953 for ``Roman
Holiday.'' Her other films include ``Breakfast at Tiffany's,'' ``My
Fair Lady,'' ``Sabrina,'' ``Funny Face,'' ``Charade,'' ``The Nun's
Story,'' ``Wait Until Dark,'' and ``Two for the Road.''
   Universal announced the addition Thursday.
   Currently filming in Los Angeles, Montana and the state of
Washington, ``Always'' is directed by Spielberg and produced by
Spielberg, Frank Marshall and Kathleen Kennedy. Richard Vane is
co-producer.
