<FIRST>r w AM-WheatProgram     07-28 0125</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Wheat Program,110</SECOND>
<HEAD>No Change in Wheat Acreage Reduction Program</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   There will be no change in the 5 percent
acreage reduction program for wheat in 1990, Agriculture Secretary
Clayton Yeutter announced Friday.
   Yeutter had set the 5 percent reduction _ the amount of land
farmers have to idle to qualify for federal supports _ on May 31,
just before the June 1 deadline. The law allows the percentage to
be adjusted if there is a significant change in the wheat supply.
   ``While severe drought has reduced wheat production, the
expected supply-demand balance has changed little since the end of
May and does not require a change in the previously announced wheat
acreage recution program for 1990,'' he said in a statement.
</TEXT>
