<HEAD>Navy Ship To Be Commissioned</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The amphibious assault ship Wasp will be
commissioned Saturday at Norfolk, Va., the Navy announced Friday.
   The 844-foot-long ship is the first of a new class of
multipurpose assault ships, which are primarily designed for use by
Marines, amphibious vehicles, and helicopters.
   Marine Commandant Gen. Alfred M. Gray will be the featured
speaker at the ceremony at the Norfolk Naval Base.
   The ship will be the 10th vessel in Navy history to carry the
name Wasp. The last Wasp was an aircraft carrier that was
decommissioned in 1972.
</TEXT>
