<HEAD>Commerce Aide Named to New Job</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush on Friday announced he will
name Shellyn Gae McCaffrey, an associate deputy secretary of
commerce, as U.S. representative on the governing body of the
International Labor Office.
   The White House said Bush was nominating her for the rank of
ambassador in her capacity as head of the U.S. delegation to the
International Labor Conference.
   She previously worked under President Reagan at the White House
as deputy executive secretary for the Economic Policy Council and
senior staff member in the Office of Policy Development.
