transformation from a conglomerate to a media company, announcing
it had sold its financial services arm, The Associates, to Ford
Motor Co. for $3.35 billion.
   Paramount said Thursday the deal would give it an after-tax gain
of $1.3 billion. When the company announced plans to sell The
Associates in April, it said it planned to use the money to finance
acquisitions.
</TEXT>
