<SECOND>PM-Treasury Bills,0097</SECOND>
<HEAD>Interest Rates Fall</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Interest rates on 52-week Treasury bills fell
in Thursday's action to the lowest level in 13 months.
   The Treasury Department sold $9.04 billion of the bills at an
average discount rate of 7.22 percent, down from 7.58 percent at
the last auction on June 29.
   The rates were the lowest since June 30, 1988, when the one-year
bills sold for 7.04 percent.
   The new discount rate understates the actual return to investors
_ 7.75 percent with a $10,000 bill selling for $9,270.00.
