<FIRST>r f PM-S&amp;LTakeovers     07-28 0233</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-S&amp;L Takeovers,0249</SECOND>
<HEAD>FDIC Takes Over Nine More S&amp;Ls</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-S&amp;Ls, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Federal Deposit Insurance Corp. has been
named managing agent for nine savings and loan institutions,
bringing the total in the government management program to 253 in
33 states.
   The new institutions declared insolvent and placed under
government management Thursday were five in Texas, two in
Louisiana, and one each in Arkansas and Michigan.
   Federal regulators transferred all deposits, offices and
substantially all of the institutions' assets to the newly created
federal mutual institutions.
   Depositors are not affected in any way by the action and can
continue to transact business as usual, federal regulators said in
announcing the action.
   The government management teams work to minimize operating
losses and ensure that the institutions are operated in a prudent
manner. The management teams will supervise operations at the
institutions until Congress approves the funding needed to sell or
merge the institutions.
   Placed in receivership Thursday and issued new charters by the
Federal Home Loan Bank Board were:
   _Capital Savings and Loan Association, West Helena, Ark.
   _Lafayette Savings and Loan Association, Gretna, La.
   _Commercial Federal Savings Bank, Hammond, La.
   _Guaranty Federal Savings Bank, Taylor. Mich.
   _Capitol City Savings Association, Austin, Texas.
   _Federal Savingsbanc of the Southwest, Kilgore, Texas.
   _New Braunfels Savings and Loan Association, New Braunfels,
Texas.
   _Hallmark Savings Association, Plano, Texas.
   _North American Savings Association, San Antonio, Texas.
</TEXT>
