<HEAD>New Chief Named at The Sporting News Publishing Co.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. LOUIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thomas G. Osenton has been named president and
chief operating officer of The Sporting News Publishing Co., a unit
of The Times Mirror Co.
   Edward E. Johnson, Times Mirror's group vice president,
announced Osenton's selection Thursday. His appointment becomes
effective Aug. 15.
   Richard Waters, current president and chief executive, has been
named chairman of the company. He will remain chief executive until
Jan. 1, when Osenton will assume those additional duties.
   Osenton currently is publisher of the American Artist Magazine,
and has worked for the ABC Television Network, including directing
the network's publicity and promotion campaign for the 1984 Winter
and Summer Olympic Games.
   The Sporting News Publishing Co. publishes The Sporting News, a
St. Louis-based weekly with a circulation of 725,000, as well as
magazines and books.
   Times Mirror is a Los Angeles-based media and information
company. It publishes the Los Angeles Times, Newsday and New York
Newsday, the Baltimore Sun newspapers, The Hartford Courant, The
Morning Call of Allentown, Pa., The (Stamford) Advocate and
Greenwich Time.
   The company also has interests in broadcast and cable
television, and book, magazine and other publishing.
